# Team 6 - Sprint 2 Planning Report

**Project:** Student Timetable Management System  
**Team Members:** Taif Jalo, Miska Voutilainen, Elias Norta, Nikita Rybakov

## Sprint Number & Dates

**Sprint Number:** Sprint 2
**Sprint Duration:** 2 Weeks (29 Jan 2026 â€“ 12 Feb 2026)

## Sprint Goal

The goal of Sprint 2 is to establish a strong technical foundation for the application. This includes creating the database schema, integrating unit testing, Maven dependency management, code coverage reporting, and creating the UI design.

## Selected Product Backlog Items

The following is a part of product backlog. Full product backlog is accessbile through [this link](https://trello.com/b/AhIEsauY/sprint-2).

- Finish UI design
- Create database schema and ER diagram
- Set up unit testing
- Configure code coverage reporting

## Planned Tasks / Breakdown

- Start UI design in Figma
- Set up unit testing
- Implementing the database
  - Design DB schema
  - Decide on technology
  - Create ER diagram
  - Seed sample data
  - CRUD testing
- Code coverage
  - Set up JaCoCo
  - Creating & running unit tests
  - Export & publish HTML report
- Set up Sprint 2 board lists:
  - Sprint 2 Backlog, Done, Pending, In Progress, Postponed
- We write Project Vision & Goal & Objective & Plan
- Document agreed decisions in Trello and GitHub

## Team Capacity & Assumptions

For Sprint 2, the team members agreed to:

- Work a few hours togther on **Sundays and Mondays** also working individually during the two-week Sprint 2 period
- Meetings are conducted via **Discord**
- Smaller meetings may occur when at least two members are available
- Working hours are recorded individually in a **shared Excel file**
- All development and planning activities are performed collaboratively during meetings and individual work sessions.

**Additional note:**
Initial planning artifacts, including the **Sprint w Planning and Review docs**, **Product Goal & Backlog & Sprint w boards**, **Trello Workspace setup**, and a **draft Use Case Diagram**, were prepared by the **Scrum Master** to support efficient collaboration. These artifacts were later reviewed, refined, and agreed upon by the entire team.

## Definition of Done

A Sprint 2 task is considered done when:

- The task objectives are completed and reviewed by the team.
- The related artifact (document, diagram, or setup) is finalized.
- The task is moved to the "Done" column in Trello.
- Relevant documentation is available in the project repository.

_Definition of done is specified in every Trello stories._
